ODE XX

TO PYRRHUS

OOLHARDY Pyrrhus, to distress

Cubs of Gaetulian lioness! Soon, dastard spoiler, shalt thou yield The battlefield.

If, winding through the rival band

To seek Nearchus, she be scanned,

How sharp the match! will you, or she, The conqueror be?

Thy nimble arrows from the sheath

Draufst thou? she sharpens grinding teeth:

Beneath the umpire’s foot the prize Dishonoured lies;
